# Direct runtime dependencies — the intended source of truth.
#
# `requirements.txt` next to this file is an unfiltered `pip freeze` inherited from the
# original scaffold: 126 packages, of which roughly 60 are never imported by any module
# in this backend (AI SDKs, AWS, pandas/numpy, and the dev toolchain). See
# SECURITY_AUDIT.md → "Stale code and dependencies" for the itemised list.
#
# Regenerate the lockfile from this file rather than from a freeze of a working venv:
#
#   pip install pip-tools
#   pip-compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt
#   pip-sync requirements.txt
#
# Verify afterwards with `python -c "import server"` and the test suite.

# --- Web framework ---
# starlette < 0.40 is affected by CVE-2024-47874 (unbounded multipart parts -> DoS),
# reachable through POST /api/admin/uploads. fastapi's own floor is >=0.37.2, and the
# resolver will happily pick that floor, so starlette is constrained explicitly here —
# do not drop this line when bumping fastapi.
fastapi>=0.115
starlette>=0.40
uvicorn[standard]>=0.30
python-multipart>=0.0.18

# --- Data layer ---
motor>=3.3.1
pymongo>=4.6.3
pydantic>=2.13

